xtract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be spacious"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to make room for"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to clear (the space), to expand","examples":[{"text":"بعد أن وافق المريض الروسي فاليري سبيريدونوف على التطوّع لإجراء العملية، واستبدال جسده المصاب بمرض ضمور العضلات والأعصاب، بجسد إنسان سليم ولكن ميت دماغياً، فإنه اعتذر أخيراً عن قراره، وتنحّى جانباً ليُفسح المجال إلى مريض آخر، ولكن من الصين.","english":"After the Russian patient Vladimir Spiridonov agreed to volunteer in the performance of the process and the replacement of his body affected by muscle and nerve dystrophy by a body of a healthy but brain-dead man, he ultimately apologized for his decision and stepped aside to make room for another patient, but from China."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of فَسَحَ (fasaḥa) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/fa.su.ħa/","/fa.sa.ħa/","/fas.sa.ħa/","/fasħ/"]}